{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"http://ghost.local:8000","title":"Ghost Docs","description":"Everything you need to know about working with the Ghost professional publishing platform."}},"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"@site","date":"2018-10-01","date_pretty":"01 October, 2018","path":null,"meta_title":"Ghost Handlebars Theme Helpers: @site","meta_description":"How to access global data properties with @site in your Ghost theme. Read more ðŸ‘‰","image":null,"next":null,"sidebar":"handlebars","toc":null,"keywords":["api","handlebars","themes","helpers"]},"html":"<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">@site</code> property provides access to global settings, which are available anywhere in your theme:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.url}}</code> â€“ the url specified for this site in your custom config file</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.title}}</code> â€“ the site title from general settings</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.description}}</code> â€“ the site description from general settings</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.icon}}</code> - The publication icon from general settings</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.logo}}</code> â€“ the site logo from general settings</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.cover_image}}</code> â€“ the site cover image from general settings</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.twitter}}</code> â€“ the twitter URL from general settings</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.facebook}}</code> â€“ the facebook URL from general settings</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.navigation}}</code> â€“ the navigation information configured in settings/design</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.timezone}}</code> â€“ the timezone as configured in general settings</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">{{@site.lang}}</code> - the configured site language.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"example-code\"><a h